# wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/Recommended_applications has some great recommendations

# command-line
# cvlc - see VLC
dot - graph drawing
epub.py - command-line epub reader - github.com/rupa/epub
mc - midnight commander
moc/mocp - command-line music player, run `mocp` for the client
mpg123 - command-line mpeg-audio player
mpv
ogg123 - command-line ogg player
pandoc - universal markdown converter
parcellite - X clipboard (works in I3, icon bottom-right)
pdfgrep - search multiple pdfs for text
powertop - battery monitor
recordmydesktop - simple tool, records to .ogv. use --windowid
sox - command line audio
spacemacs - vim+emacs
svox pico2wave - great text-to-speech!
tmux
xdotool - cmdline mouse automation
vlc - more powerful than cvlc, type help to see commands. instant support for internet radio (mp3, mp3a, ...)

# gui
ttrss
chrome:
- ublock origin
- keyboard shortcuts to reorder tabs

windowed environment
--------------------
use mouse keys (keypad controls mouse)
